&quot;Gestalt is the primary attribute of life&quot;– Ludwig von Bertalanffy, &quot;Kritische Theorie der Formbildung&quot; (1928)

&quot;Friedrich Nietzsche saw—through the mists of his contempt for all things English—an even more cosmic message in Darwin: God is dead. If Nietzsche is the father of existentialism, then perhaps Darwin deserves the title of grandfather.&quot;
– Daniel Dennett, &quot;Darwin's Dangerous Idea&quot; (1995), Chap. 3 : Universal Acid

&quot;Our experiments [by the artists of 'Cobra'] the aim at letting thought express itself spontaneously without the control which reason represents. By means of this irrational spontaneity we get closer to the vital source of life. Our goal is to liberate ourselves from the control of reason which has been and still is the thing which the bourgeoisie has idealized to seize control of life.&quot;
– Asger Jorn (1949) in 'Discours aux pingouins' ('Speech to the Penguins'), in 'Cobra' 1. (1949)
